  "id": "phekb-epilepsy-dx",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "epilepsy",
  "name": "Epilepsy - Diagnosis Code Query (Multi-Subtype)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find epilepsy patients via diagnosis codes. Epilepsy is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by clinical pattern: parent epilepsy, generalized epilepsy, seizure disorder, status epilepticus, and the broader epileptic seizure finding. Synthea distributes patients across these subtypes.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients diagnosed with epilepsy, including generalized epilepsy, seizure disorder, status epilepticus, and epileptic seizure findings.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with epilepsy.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of epilepsy or seizure disorder \u2014 including the parent epilepsy concept, generalized epilepsy, seizure disorder, status epilepticus (a neurological emergency), and the broader epileptic seizure finding.",
    "expert": "I need to identify all epilepsy patients. Epilepsy is documented under multiple SNOMED codes: Epilepsy (84757009) is the parent concept, with subtype-specific Generalized epilepsy (19598007), Seizure disorder (128613002), Status epilepticus (230456007), and the finding-level Epileptic seizure (313307000). Search Condition resources for all five codes."
  },
